â€¢ foundry.md â€“ This markdown file provides an overview of the available commands and the machine interface (tool calls) for the client.
â€¢ welcome.txt â€“ A welcome banner displayed on startup.
â€¢ LICENSE.txt and build.bat â€“ These files establish project licensing (MIT License) and build instructions for compiling the Deno application.
â€¢ The â€œforgeâ€ subdirectory is used for storing file submissions and conversation snapshots.
â€¢ The â€œisolationâ€ subdirectory contains a sandbox for testing code execution, distinct from the main workflow.

5. Summary

The Nitrologic Foundry Client is a robust research tool designed for interacting with language models while integrating file sharing and conversation management. With its modular tool calls, command interface, and detailed configuration options, it becomes a flexible environment for testing model capabilities â€“ particularly for those models that support an interactive tools interface. The design elegantly combines interactive terminal I/O, file system operations, and API integrations in a portable Deno runtime environment.

