â€¢ File Sharing and Submission  
â€ƒâ€“ The â€œ/shareâ€ command enables users to designate files or directories for sharing. Individual files are processed (for text, JSON, markdown, etc.) or converted to Base64 for binary content.  
â€ƒâ€“ A sharing mechanism tracks file metadata (path, size, modification time, hash) and tags shared files.  
â€ƒâ€“ The client supports a â€œ/pushâ€ or â€œ/commitâ€ command that scans shared files, detects modifications or deletions, andâ€”if changes are detectedâ€”updates the chat history and files submitted for review.

â€¢ Configuration and Customization  
â€ƒâ€“ Several configuration flags allow toggling features such as committing shares on start, ANSI rendering of markdown, slow output, verbose debugging information, and logging (to a file â€œfoundry.logâ€).  
â€ƒâ€“ The â€œ/configâ€ command lists available flags, which include:  
â€ƒâ€ƒâ€¢ commitonstartâ€‚ (commit shared files on start)  
â€ƒâ€ƒâ€¢ toolsâ€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚(enable model tool interface)  
â€ƒâ€ƒâ€¢ ansiâ€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚(render using ANSI/markdown)  
â€ƒâ€ƒâ€¢ slowâ€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚â€‚(output at reading speed)  
